To:	Mr. Miguel Juan Sebastian Pinera Echenique
From:	Fund ‚ÄúMiddle class support & development‚Äù
Date:	September 1, 2017
Re.:	Cooperation in escape of miners in Mirniy (Yakutiya) using the experience of Chile of 2010

Dear Mr. Miguel Juan Sebastian Pinera Echenique,

Hereby we would like to express our sincere respect to you and inform you about the following.

Today we discussed with Chief of the Ministry of Emergency Situations in Yakutiya (Russia), the rescue operations in Mirniy (Yakutiya, Russia) of 8 miners disappeared deep underground in the mine after the accident on August 4, 2017 and agreed to apply to Chile to cooperate on the successful experience of Chile in escape of 33 Chilean miners in the Copiapo mining accident rescue operations in 2010.

We would appreciate your cooperation to bring the escape team to Mirniy (Yakutiya, Russia) and use the escape methods that were successful in 2010.

The accident in Mirniy happened on August 4, 2017. The accident in Chile in 2010 happened on August 5. In 2010 after 17 days of escape the Chilean miners were considered dead but then the escape operations renewed and all miners were found and escaped on October 13, 2010 after 69 days. In Mirniy 8 miners were considered dead this week because they were not found after 21 days of escape operations. In case your experts who participated in 2010 agree to assist the escape operations may be renewed.

Our Fund ‚ÄúMiddle class support & development‚Äù was established in 2005 by V.Chernomyrdin, Prime Minister of Russia in 1992-1998, for support of science, technologies, education, culture and international cooperation.

Looking forward our joint efforts and with kind regards,

Andrey Chernomyrdin			Alex Chupilkin,
